metadata.name: NounishWebb2 1
metadata.description:
A Nounish creation by @profwerder adding some cc0 Nouns traits to one of the first James Webb Space Telescope image released into the public domain. Learn more about Nouns at: https://nouns.wtf/

Note: Nounish additions are obviously not representative of actual placement of IRL planets, void, flamingos etc.

From https://webb.nasa.gov/
The James Webb Space Telescope is an international collaboration between NASA, the European Space Agency and the Canadian Space Agency. The Space Telescope Science Institute is the science and mission operations center for Webb.
Background image Credits: NASA, ESA, CSA, and STScI Learn more at: https://webb.nasa.gov/

Background Image Description: A group of five galaxies that appear close to each other in the sky: two in the middle, one toward the top, one to the upper left, and one toward the bottom. Four of the five appear to be touching. One is somewhat separated. In the image, the galaxies are large relative to the hundreds of much smaller (more distant) galaxies in the background. All five galaxies have bright white cores. Each has a slightly different size, shape, structure, and coloring. Scattered across the image, in front of the galaxies are number of foreground stars with diffraction spikes: bright white points, each with eight bright lines radiating out from the center.
